This paper discusses regularized support vector machines (SVMs) and their equivalence to a new robust optimization formulation. The paper focuses on the algorithms and analysis of SVMs, which are topics commonly found in the machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the implications of robustness and regularization in SVMs, which are topics commonly found in the neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.DS, followed by cs.NE, cs.AI, and cs.SI.
